<HEADLINE>
GREAT RIVER QUEEN TO OFFER LUXURY TOURS ON DANSHUI RIVER
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 31 (CNA) 05/31/07  18:16:51 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
Great River Queen, a newly completed luxury cruise boat owned by
the Great River Tourism Co., will begin to offer sightseeing
tours combined with five-star food along the Danshui river in
northern Taiwan from June 1.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the company said Thursday that the three-deck
passenger barge, based at Guandu Wharf, will operate four tours a
day, each lasing about two hours.
</P>
<P>
He said that in addition to lunch, afternoon tea and dinner
cruises, there will be a narrated sightseeing tour every morning
to let students and social groups understand the history and
unique ecology of the river.
</P>
<P>
The normal full prices are NT$1,550 per head for a weekday tour
and NT$1,880 for a tour on a weekend or holiday, with food and
drink included, the spokesman said, adding that the company will
allow a 20 percent discount throughout June.
</P>
<P>
The spokeswoman also said all food served on the boat will be
prepared by chefs from the Sheraton Taipei Hotel, which is noted
for its gourmet cooking, and that passengers will also be able to
listen to live music while they enjoy the views along the river
</P>
<P>
The 500-ton boat, built by San Yang Shipbuilding Co., carries a
price tag of NT$150 million. Measuring 40.5 meters long and 10
meters wide, with a maximum designed speed of 12 knots, the boat
can accommodate up to 320 passengers.
</P>
